when Emmy sat on your lap.

142
00:08:51,431 --> 00:08:53,399
You smell like an ash tray.

143
00:09:01,208 --> 00:09:03,513
Mama, I got to talk
to you about something.

144
00:09:03,543 --> 00:09:04,815
Talk.

145
00:09:04,845 --> 00:09:06,783
I wanna go live with
Aunt Marlene in Chicago.

146
00:09:06,813 --> 00:09:08,585
-You wanna what?
-I've been thinking about it

147
00:09:08,615 --> 00:09:10,954
for a long time.
I could go to school there.

148
00:09:10,984 --> 00:09:13,590
-Lucy could look after me.
-Lucy?

149
00:09:13,620 --> 00:09:16,126
Go to school, mama.
My teachers down here

150
00:09:16,156 --> 00:09:18,562
don't even speak good English
at English class.

151
00:09:18,592 --> 00:09:20,263
Get ready for college
that way.

152
00:09:20,293 --> 00:09:22,399
What brought this on?

153
00:09:22,429 --> 00:09:24,797
-Nothing.
-Nothing?

154
00:09:24,865 --> 00:09:26,299
Yeah.

155
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:29,206
Girl, you ain't going nowhere.

156
00:09:29,236 --> 00:09:31,742
And you got the sense
God give a chicken.

157
00:09:31,772 --> 00:09:33,377
I make straight A's.

158
00:09:33,407 --> 00:09:34,978
Yeah, book smart,
not people smart.

159
00:09:35,008 --> 00:09:36,747
You ain't got
no common sense, Emerald.

160
00:09:36,777 --> 00:09:38,849
You like to make me
feel small.

161
00:09:38,879 --> 00:09:40,880
Emerald Marie Delacroix.

162
00:09:41,014 --> 00:09:43,750
-What'd you just say?
-Nothing.

163
00:09:44,017 --> 00:09:46,920
Don't you accuse me
of making you feel small.

164
00:09:47,454 --> 00:09:48,658
Yes, ma'am.

165
00:09:48,688 --> 00:09:52,458
And don't you yes, ma'am me
either with that tone.

166
00:09:53,393 --> 00:09:55,995
I don't know what you want me
to say, mama.

167
00:09:56,063 --> 00:09:58,064
I make you feel small.

168
00:09:59,466 --> 00:10:01,067
And why is that?

169
00:10:01,334 --> 00:10:03,169
Go on, tell the truth.

170
00:10:05,372 --> 00:10:07,574
Because it makes you feel big.

171
00:10:09,042 --> 00:10:13,817
Well then,
you ain't going nowhere.

172
00:10:13,847 --> 00:10:16,583
Just stay right here with me.

173
00:10:54,454 --> 00:10:56,159
Are you Mr. Robicheaux?

174
00:10:56,189 --> 00:10:57,427
How you all doing?

175
00:10:57,457 --> 00:10:58,695
Fine.

176
00:10:58,725 --> 00:11:01,094
Just making sure
everything's okay.

177
00:11:01,862 --> 00:11:04,000
Everything's fine.
Why don't you come on in?

178
00:11:04,030 --> 00:11:07,971
Not tonight. I saw Noogie
in New Orleans.

179
00:11:08,001 --> 00:11:10,103
Singing for Allen Toussaint.

180
00:11:10,370 --> 00:11:13,940
-Who you got?
-A fella by the name of Dupre.

181
00:11:14,040 --> 00:11:15,775
White boy?

182
00:11:16,610 --> 00:11:18,244
Unusual.

183
00:11:31,758 --> 00:11:33,626
How y'all doing?

184
00:11:33,693 --> 00:11:35,995
Let's get the party started.

185
00:11:37,964 --> 00:11:39,799
Mes ami, hey.

186
00:11:40,133 --> 00:11:41,801
Ms. Ruby!

187
00:12:00,487 --> 00:12:02,455
Have a good time.

188
00:12:15,101 --> 00:12:16,973
Bonner, I want you to come by

189
00:12:17,003 --> 00:12:19,972
and do some work for me
next week. All right.

190
00:12:24,244 --> 00:12:25,916
Ladies and gentlemen,

191
00:12:25,946 --> 00:12:28,885
I have some good news
and I have some good news.

192
00:12:28,915 --> 00:12:30,854
