called me pretty.

204
00:15:50,283 --> 00:15:51,817
Well,

205
00:15:54,621 --> 00:15:56,326
I must be out of my mind then.

206
00:15:56,356 --> 00:15:59,058
Yeah, there's always
a possibility.

207
00:16:00,393 --> 00:16:03,500
-I just wanted to say thanks.
-For what?

208
00:16:03,530 --> 00:16:05,598
You forced me into it.

209
00:16:07,801 --> 00:16:11,370
Hey, you got
my driver's license?

210
00:16:11,704 --> 00:16:14,477
-Yup.
-Can I have it?

211
00:16:14,507 --> 00:16:16,809
Uh-hmm.
End of the evening.

212
00:16:17,644 --> 00:16:20,049
What? I ain't gonna
skip out on you.

213
00:16:20,079 --> 00:16:23,015
Good. So you'll be here
the end of the evening.

214
00:16:24,617 --> 00:16:26,152
Hey, Dup!

215
00:16:26,486 --> 00:16:28,258
Come on, man,
we're waiting on you.

216
00:16:28,288 --> 00:16:30,890
Yeah, I'll be right there.

217
00:16:32,926 --> 00:16:35,131
- Ruby.
-Hey there.

218
00:16:35,161 --> 00:16:36,829
Hey.

219
00:16:37,897 --> 00:16:38,968
What do you want?

220
00:16:38,998 --> 00:16:41,104
What time are you leaving
in the morning, Earl?

221
00:16:41,134 --> 00:16:43,035
My ride comes at 7:00.

222
00:16:43,403 --> 00:16:45,875
Earl, you're the only man
go offshore

223
00:16:45,905 --> 00:16:48,011
for two weeks
that go on two months.

224
00:16:48,041 --> 00:16:50,980
-Don't start.
-Why is that then?

225
00:16:51,010 --> 00:16:53,049
I stay for the overtime,
you know that.

226
00:16:53,079 --> 00:16:55,118
They don't keep nobody
out there that long,

227
00:16:55,148 --> 00:16:56,753
they just don't do it.

228
00:16:56,783 --> 00:16:59,418
