Two, three, four.

231
00:17:14,367 --> 00:17:15,868
Hey.

232
00:18:00,480 --> 00:18:01,981
May I?

233
00:18:21,935 --> 00:18:23,436
Shit.

234
00:19:16,789 --> 00:19:18,858
What's up?
How you doing?

235
00:19:26,899 --> 00:19:28,801
Here you go.

236
00:19:33,273 --> 00:19:34,874
Thank you.

237
00:19:42,215 --> 00:19:43,883
Yeah, hold on.

238
00:20:35,501 --> 00:20:37,836
What you doing here, Ms. Betty?

239
00:20:38,171 --> 00:20:40,372
Just came to hear him sing.

240
00:20:40,573 --> 00:20:42,145
Yeah, but this ain't no
place for you.

241
00:20:42,175 --> 00:20:43,646
Jack,
get her out of here,

242
00:20:43,676 --> 00:20:45,181
there's more
to notion with him,

243
00:20:45,211 --> 00:20:46,983
I don't need no trouble
in here now.

244
00:20:47,013 --> 00:20:48,781
I'm not hurting anybody.

245
00:20:48,881 --> 00:20:50,186
All right.

246
00:20:50,216 --> 00:20:52,318
Sing. Keep playing.

247
00:20:52,919 --> 00:20:54,787
Hey, Jack.

248
00:20:55,254 --> 00:20:56,592
Jack.

249
00:20:56,622 --> 00:20:58,227
Maybe we could
take it easy, Ruby.

250
00:20:58,257 --> 00:20:59,462
Get her out of here.

251
00:20:59,492 --> 00:21:01,160
Oh, Jack.

252
00:21:01,260 --> 00:21:03,900
Damn.
Come on, Ms. Betty,

253
00:21:03,930 --> 00:21:06,165
-I'm gonna take you home.
-No.

254
00:21:06,999 --> 00:21:10,006
Take it easy.
Take it easy, Ms. Betty.

255
00:21:10,036 --> 00:21:11,874
That is my husband.

256
00:21:11,904 --> 00:21:13,405
Yes, it is.

257
00:21:13,506 --> 00:21:15,978
- That is my husband.
- The show's not over.

258
00:21:16,008 --> 00:21:18,081
No, it's not over,
I'm not going home.

259
00:21:18,111 --> 00:21:21,480
I don't want--
don't, please leave me alone.

260
00:21:26,786 --> 00:21:28,491
Let go of me. Let go of me.

261
00:21:28,521 --> 00:21:30,289
I'm not holding her.

262
00:21:30,623 --> 00:21:31,828
Let's just go.

263
00:21:31,858 --> 00:21:33,596
