No.

791
01:08:01,444 --> 01:08:02,516
Sure?

792
01:08:02,546 --> 01:08:05,252
I'd have enough trouble
to be talking to a white man

793
01:08:05,282 --> 01:08:07,387
in the middle of the night.

794
01:08:07,417 --> 01:08:09,552
Well, what trouble you got?

795
01:08:11,321 --> 01:08:12,989
Nothing.

796
01:08:13,156 --> 01:08:14,891
Ruby.

797
01:08:15,525 --> 01:08:17,063
What's going on?

798
01:08:17,093 --> 01:08:19,495
Well, what do you want from me?

799
01:08:20,630 --> 01:08:23,166
Go home to your wife.

800
01:08:42,185 --> 01:08:44,287
It's crowded over there.

801
01:08:50,193 --> 01:08:52,962
Come on, darling. Come on.

802
01:08:53,964 --> 01:08:55,631
No.

803
01:08:56,232 --> 01:08:59,569
You're wild, little thing.
I like that.

804
01:09:00,270 --> 01:09:02,609
-Come on, let's go.
-No. Get off of me.

805
01:09:02,639 --> 01:09:04,844
-Come on, let's go.
-Get off of me.

806
01:09:04,874 --> 01:09:07,013
-Let go of me.
-What?

807
01:09:07,043 --> 01:09:09,011
May I cut in?

808
01:09:21,725 --> 01:09:23,459
15?

809
01:09:28,665 --> 01:09:30,700
What you all staring at?

810
01:09:47,651 --> 01:09:50,653
It's okay, it's okay.

811
01:09:53,256 --> 01:09:54,327
It's Emerald.

812
01:09:54,357 --> 01:09:55,895
-Is she--
-She had enough.

813
01:09:55,925 --> 01:09:58,327
Emerald, Emerald.

814
01:10:00,196 --> 01:10:02,331
Are you okay?

815
01:10:05,335 --> 01:10:07,937
You know,
the funny thing is,

816
01:10:08,872 --> 01:10:12,545
I raised her to have
all this spirit, this spunk,

817
01:10:12,575 --> 01:10:15,978
and every time she shows that,
I just get so scared.

818
01:10:17,814 --> 01:10:18,852
And I know this world

819
01:10:18,882 --> 01:10:21,684
is gonna try to bring her down
to her knees.

820
01:10:27,691 --> 01:10:29,692
I thought they'd be back by now.

821
01:10:30,360 --> 01:10:32,829
You're such a little momma,
you know that?

822
01:10:36,066 --> 01:10:37,700
You got children?

823
01:10:42,338 --> 01:10:44,140
We had one...

824
01:10:46,042 --> 01:10:47,677
but we lost her.

825
01:10:48,311 --> 01:10:49,812
Sorry.

826
01:10:52,148 --> 01:10:54,550
Betty was in a car wreck and...

827
01:10:56,820 --> 01:10:58,754
she flew sideways and...

828
01:10:59,956 --> 01:11:01,691
hit the baby and...

829
01:11:03,526 --> 01:11:05,995
died instantly.

830
01:11:08,164 --> 01:11:12,072
Thing is, I was passed out
in a barn,

831
01:11:12,102 --> 01:11:14,070
they were coming to pick me up.

832
01:11:17,340 --> 01:11:19,742
So, it's all your fault.

833
01:11:21,711 --> 01:11:23,379
Three...

834
01:11:23,813 --> 01:11:25,481
four seconds...

835
01:11:26,683 --> 01:11:28,517
been a different world.

836
01:11:31,721 --> 01:11:34,728
See, I can't seem to shake
those three seconds.

837
01:11:34,758 --> 01:11:36,259
Hmm.

838
01:11:37,494 --> 01:11:42,368
You know, sometimes all it takes
is a few seconds

839
01:11:42,398 --> 01:11:45,067
to turn your life
in the right direction.

840
01:11:50,707 --> 01:11:52,208
One...

841
01:12:01,084 --> 01:12:02,585
two...

842
01:12:22,172 --> 01:12:23,806
Where have you been?

843
01:12:26,743 --> 01:12:28,844
Girl, where have you been?

844
01:12:29,145 --> 01:12:30,717
Over at Petrie's.

845
01:12:30,747 --> 01:12:31,951
And how did you get there?

846
01:12:31,981 --> 01:12:34,016
And you better
tell me the truth.

847
01:12:34,050 --> 01:12:35,088
Hitchhiked.

848
01:12:35,118 --> 01:12:37,490
Girl,
have you lost your mind?

849
01:12:37,520 --> 01:12:39,325
Do you know where you are?

850
01:12:39,355 --> 01:12:42,729
This is the segregated south
and you are a negro.

851
01:12:42,759 --> 01:12:44,430
It's the middle of the night.

852
01:12:44,460 --> 01:12:47,767
I will not have my daughter
beat and rape as a joke

853
01:12:47,797 --> 01:12:48,968
by some drunk white man.

854
01:12:48,998 --> 01:12:52,238
-Ma, I'm all right.
-By the grace of God, Emerald,

855
01:12:52,268 --> 01:12:53,373
I could just beat you.

856
01:12:53,403 --> 01:12:55,775
I could just shake you
until you get some sense.

857
01:12:55,805 --> 01:12:58,144
-I'm sorry.
-Go to your room before I decide

858
01:12:58,174 --> 01:12:59,942
to beat you right now.

859
01:13:00,577 --> 01:13:02,048
Please don't talk to me
like that.

860
01:13:02,078 --> 01:13:04,083
I'll talk to you
any way I want to.

861
01:13:04,113 --> 01:13:05,614
No.

862
01:13:07,584 --> 01:13:10,152
I'm sorry I disappointed you.

863
01:13:11,087 --> 01:13:15,391
But I'm not a dog,
so don't talk to me like one.

864
01:13:19,562 --> 01:13:24,400
Jack, Bootsie, I owe you.

865
01:13:24,434 --> 01:13:26,569
You don't owe me
nothing, sheriff.

866
01:13:27,670 --> 01:13:29,472
-Good night.
-Good night.

867
01:13:32,976 --> 01:13:34,810
Well, hey, Dupre.

868
01:13:35,712 --> 01:13:37,480
You had some night.

869
01:13:38,248 --> 01:13:40,416
Just keeping her company
while she wait.

870
01:13:41,384 --> 01:13:44,086
-I'm heading out.
-Good.

871
01:13:44,254 --> 01:13:45,625
Bonsoir.

872
01:13:45,655 --> 01:13:48,457
-Bonsoir.
-Bonsoir, mon ami.

873
01:13:59,802 --> 01:14:01,303
Mommy.

874
01:14:05,174 --> 01:14:07,143
I'm sorry, Emerald.

875
01:14:09,178 --> 01:14:11,013
I'm sorry, too.

876
01:14:12,515 --> 01:14:14,483
But I'm not sorry.

877
01:14:20,990 --> 01:14:24,660
It's hard to know
what's right to do sometimes.

878
01:15:33,363 --> 01:15:34,997
What are you doing?

879
01:15:35,732 --> 01:15:40,002
I don't know.
I see your light on and...

880
01:15:40,903 --> 01:15:43,205
I mean, you still got
my driver's license.

881
01:15:46,843 --> 01:15:49,245
-Can I come in?
-Emerald's asleep.

882
01:15:54,784 --> 01:15:56,285
Come.

883
01:16:27,717 --> 01:16:29,885
I can't do this.

884
01:16:30,853 --> 01:16:31,958
Why?

885
01:16:31,988 --> 01:16:34,890
Because people
get killed for it, that's why.

886
01:16:38,561 --> 01:16:40,296
You're a handsome man.

887
01:16:41,297 --> 01:16:42,831
Well, thank you.

888
01:16:45,935 --> 01:16:47,740
Women
tell you that often?

889
01:16:47,770 --> 01:16:48,941
No.

890
01:16:48,971 --> 01:16:50,472
Don't lie.

891
01:16:54,243 --> 01:16:55,744
I'm sorry.

892
01:16:55,812 --> 01:16:58,581
You won't be sorry
for telling the truth.

893
01:17:01,551 --> 01:17:04,687
From all the goings-on
around here, I see.

894
01:17:05,655 --> 01:17:07,323
I ain't like that.

895
01:17:11,894 --> 01:17:14,263
Couldn't stop thinking
about you.

896
01:17:20,770 --> 01:17:23,138
All I wanna do
is touch you again.

897
01:17:25,908 --> 01:17:28,177
I never been
with another man.

898
01:17:29,078 --> 01:17:30,183
Save myself for marriage

899
01:17:30,213 --> 01:17:32,815
and then kept my promise
ever since.

900
01:17:33,516 --> 01:17:36,552
Now, can you feature that?

901
01:17:38,454 --> 01:17:42,491
Road house queen
of St. Mary parish.

902
01:17:46,162 --> 01:17:48,101
Got no idea
how beautiful you are, do you?

903
01:17:48,131 --> 01:17:49,569
Hmm.

904
01:17:49,599 --> 01:17:51,200
No, you don't.

905
01:17:53,836 --> 01:17:55,604
How long you'd been hiding?

906
01:17:58,441 --> 01:18:00,175
How long you'd been waiting?

907
01:18:02,678 --> 01:18:03,783
I see you, Ruby.

908
01:18:03,813 --> 01:18:05,685
I don't understand
why I feel like

909
01:18:05,715 --> 01:18:09,355
I know you.
I don't know you.

910
01:18:09,385 --> 01:18:10,423
You do know me.

911
01:18:10,453 --> 01:18:13,389
I know you make me feel
like I'm crazy.

912
01:18:13,589 --> 01:18:15,591
Like I don't wanna...

913
01:18:36,612 --> 01:18:38,313
Shine, Ruby.

914
01:18:42,084 --> 01:18:43,652
Do I?

915
01:19:05,875 --> 01:19:08,110
Shh. Come on.

916
01:19:25,361 --> 01:19:29,735
I smell like cigarettes
and beer.

917
01:19:29,765 --> 01:19:33,368
Me, too. So, what?

918
01:19:36,906 --> 01:19:38,144
Uh...

919
01:19:38,174 --> 01:19:39,808
I'm not--

920
01:19:41,477 --> 01:19:44,947
I mean, if you don't want.

921
01:21:37,993 --> 01:21:40,166
Shh. Shh. Shh.
You're gonna wake Emerald.

922
01:21:40,196 --> 01:21:41,600
You're the one
making all the noise.

923
01:21:41,630 --> 01:21:43,769
-Well, if you stay away from me.
-You know I can't.

924
01:21:43,799 --> 01:21:45,171
No. No. No. No. No.

925
01:21:45,201 --> 01:21:47,340
If you tickle me one more time
I'mma lose my mind.

926
01:21:47,370 --> 01:21:50,376
You got a weakness
and I found it. Come here.

927
01:21:50,406 --> 01:21:52,345
No. No. No.

928
01:21:52,375 --> 01:21:55,811
-Don't you tickle me.
-Okay. Okay.

929
01:21:56,145 --> 01:21:59,047
Promise. No more tickling
behind the knees.

930
01:21:59,682 --> 01:22:02,718
You're the devil
and I don't believe you.

931
01:22:05,054 --> 01:22:07,222
Open the door.

932
01:22:08,691 --> 01:22:10,726
Open the door.

933
01:22:11,160 --> 01:22:12,365
Bar's closed.

934
01:22:12,395 --> 01:22:15,364
Sounds to me like you're
doing some business in there.

935
01:22:15,531 --> 01:22:16,569
This is my place.

936
01:22:16,599 --> 01:22:18,637
I want you gone,
I'mma call the sheriff.

937
01:22:18,667 --> 01:22:21,307
I don't think you have to do
that with a white man in there.

938
01:22:21,337 --> 01:22:23,438
-I'll go ahead back.
-Go.

939
01:22:24,240 --> 01:22:26,112
You got to get her out of here.

940
01:22:26,142 --> 01:22:28,043
Billy!

941
01:22:28,077 --> 01:22:29,682
Billy,
I've got to tell you something.

942
01:22:29,712 --> 01:22:31,117
I'll go get my things.

943
01:22:31,147 --> 01:22:33,315
I need to talk to you.

944
01:22:33,582 --> 01:22:36,785
Dupre, open the door.

945
01:22:36,886 --> 01:22:39,425
Billy, please open the door.

946
01:22:39,455 --> 01:22:44,459
He's coming.
He'll be here in a minute.

947
01:23:21,063 --> 01:23:23,265
I want you to listen to me.

948
01:23:25,601 --> 01:23:27,502
You never listen to me.

949
01:23:30,439 --> 01:23:32,374
When you stay out,

950
01:23:33,476 --> 01:23:38,013
when you come home,
everything about you hurts me.

951
01:23:38,948 --> 01:23:40,820
I waited for you tonight,

952
01:23:40,850 --> 01:23:43,885
because I was gonna tell you
that I forgive you.

953
01:23:44,019 --> 01:23:46,321
And I was gonna ask you
to forgive me.

954
01:23:49,225 --> 01:23:50,926
And then you didn't come.

955
01:23:51,961 --> 01:23:55,197
And I knew that nobody's ever
gonna forgive anybody.

956
01:23:59,268 --> 01:24:01,003
What's your name?

957
01:24:03,339 --> 01:24:04,840
Ruby.

958
01:24:05,674 --> 01:24:10,545
Oh, you.
Did you enjoy my husband?

959
01:24:12,181 --> 01:24:14,950
It didn't mean anything.

960
01:24:17,219 --> 01:24:19,554
It does to me.

961
01:24:20,990 --> 01:24:22,891
Do you have a husband?

962
01:24:23,893 --> 01:24:25,394
Yes.

963
01:24:26,061 --> 01:24:27,829
Does he do this?

964
01:24:32,368 --> 01:24:33,869
Yes.

965
01:24:37,039 --> 01:24:39,474
I don't know
why it cuts me so deep.

966
01:24:39,642 --> 01:24:41,243
Betty, I...

967
01:24:43,646 --> 01:24:45,414
I'm sorry this happened.

968
01:24:47,950 --> 01:24:51,286
-I'm sorry--
-You are sorry you got caught.

969
01:24:53,155 --> 01:24:55,057
And that's it.

970
01:24:55,925 --> 01:24:57,859
Don't lie.

971
01:24:58,861 --> 01:25:00,362
Don't lie.

972
01:25:00,963 --> 01:25:02,497
You know, you're right.

973
01:25:04,533 --> 01:25:06,568
I'm not sorry it happened.

974
01:25:09,972 --> 01:25:12,140
I can't live like this anymore.

975
01:25:14,276 --> 01:25:17,283
Our son may be gone,
but you and I,

976
01:25:17,313 --> 01:25:19,548
we're both still alive.

977
01:25:19,915 --> 01:25:23,118
We can let go, hmm?

978
01:25:23,652 --> 01:25:25,387
We can let go.

979
01:25:26,422 --> 01:25:28,023
It's gonna be all right.

980
01:25:28,324 --> 01:25:30,492
Nothing will ever be
all right again.

981
01:25:31,026 --> 01:25:32,527
No.

982
01:25:35,130 --> 01:25:36,832
No.

983
01:25:44,506 --> 01:25:46,845
Stay with me. Stay with me.
Stay with me. Stay with me.

984
01:25:46,875 --> 01:25:49,978
Stay with me. Don't move.
Hold on.

985
01:25:50,145 --> 01:25:51,646
Hold on.

986
01:25:51,747 --> 01:25:53,886
Can we call somebody?

987
01:25:53,916 --> 01:25:55,617
You shot him.

988
01:25:56,051 --> 01:25:58,019
Can we get help?

989
01:25:58,354 --> 01:25:59,955
He's dead.

990
01:26:44,633 --> 01:26:46,234
Oh, man.

991
01:26:47,436 --> 01:26:48,970
Where's Ruby?

992
01:26:49,471 --> 01:26:51,006
I don't know.

993
01:26:51,740 --> 01:26:53,212
I came as fast as I could.

994
01:26:53,242 --> 01:26:54,613
What the hell
happened here, Ruby?

995
01:26:54,643 --> 01:26:56,882
Qu'est que ça?
You didn't shoot him, did you?

996
01:26:56,912 --> 01:26:58,283
She did it. But it don't matter.

997
01:26:58,313 --> 01:27:00,152
They'll get me
on my knees because of it.

998
01:27:00,182 --> 01:27:01,387
I can't let Emerald see that.

999
01:27:01,417 --> 01:27:03,188
No. Ms. Betty would tell them
what happened.

1000
01:27:03,218 --> 01:27:05,024
-She won't lie.
-I never lie.

1001
01:27:05,054 --> 01:27:06,558
You see,
she'll tell them the truth.

1002
01:27:06,588 --> 01:27:08,127
And nobody will think
you did anything.

1003
01:27:08,157 --> 01:27:10,663
It doesn't matter. They'll know
I slept with a married white man

1004
01:27:10,693 --> 01:27:13,132
and he got killed because of me.
The door is open, Johnny,

1005
01:27:13,162 --> 01:27:14,763
I'll never get it shut.

1006
01:27:14,897 --> 01:27:16,502
Earl's gone, Johnny.

1007
01:27:16,532 --> 01:27:18,170
It's just me
against all of them.

1008
01:27:18,200 --> 01:27:21,436
I got to get Emerald out of here
before it all starts.

1009
01:27:35,751 --> 01:27:37,252
Leave it.

1010
01:27:38,687 --> 01:27:40,326
I'll tell them
I was with Dupre,

1011
01:27:40,356 --> 01:27:42,661
she came, they got in a fight
and she shot him.

1012
01:27:42,691 --> 01:27:43,896
I saw everything.

1013
01:27:43,926 --> 01:27:45,497
You were in the back.
Not even here.

1014
01:27:45,527 --> 01:27:46,999
You think she's gonna lie
for me.

1015
01:27:47,029 --> 01:27:48,763
I never lie.

1016
01:27:48,897 --> 01:27:50,632
No more lies.

1017
01:27:50,699 --> 01:27:53,668
I'll never get away
if I don't do it right now.

1018
01:27:53,836 --> 01:27:56,942
Johnny, I wanna give you
the deed to my building

1019
01:27:56,972 --> 01:27:58,177
in exchange for your car.

1020
01:27:58,207 --> 01:28:00,479
But you were born here.
This is yours.

1021
01:28:00,509 --> 01:28:02,915
I won't let them take my dignity
because I forgot my place

1022
01:28:02,945 --> 01:28:04,616
-for a few minutes.

1023
01:28:04,646 --> 01:28:06,185
Because I acted human
for once.

1024
01:28:06,215 --> 01:28:07,883
Where's the phone?

1025
01:28:11,754 --> 01:28:13,255
Johnny...

1026
01:28:13,455 --> 01:28:15,027
do this favor for me.

1027
01:28:15,057 --> 01:28:16,628
Take the deed
to the Bucket of Blood.

1028
01:28:16,658 --> 01:28:18,793
No, this is too much.
Just...

1029
01:28:19,661 --> 01:28:22,464
-Just take the car.
- No, no, please.

1030
01:28:23,832 --> 01:28:25,934
I know it will be in good hands.

1031
01:28:27,069 --> 01:28:28,670
Do it for me.

1032
01:28:32,040 --> 01:28:33,541
Emerald!

1033
01:28:35,844 --> 01:28:37,445
Emerald!

1034
01:28:46,955 --> 01:28:49,891
Ma, did you shoot him?

1035
01:28:50,492 --> 01:28:52,631
-No.
-Then why are we running?

1036
01:28:52,661 --> 01:28:54,496
We're not running.

1037
01:28:59,134 --> 01:29:01,136
Ma! Leave me.

1038
01:29:02,271 --> 01:29:04,543
Don't push me down. I didn't do
anything to be ashamed of.

1039
01:29:04,573 --> 01:29:07,108
-Neither did I.
-Then don't act like it.

1040
01:29:18,353 --> 01:29:19,854
I'm doing this for you.

1041
01:29:20,088 --> 01:29:22,624
No. You're scared...

1042
01:29:23,225 --> 01:29:25,297
-like always.
-You're damn right I'm scared.

1043
01:29:25,327 --> 01:29:27,099
And smart to be scared.

1044
01:29:27,129 --> 01:29:28,734
Is it smart to run
like a criminal

1045
01:29:28,764 --> 01:29:30,936
-when you're not a criminal?
-I might risk it

1046
01:29:30,966 --> 01:29:34,202
if it was just me, but I can't
take the chance with you.

1047
01:29:37,573 --> 01:29:41,276
Your daddy, he's gone.

1048
01:29:42,110 --> 01:29:43,979
And he ain't coming back.

1049
01:29:45,147 --> 01:29:46,614
I know.

1050
01:29:49,151 --> 01:29:50,652
You knew?

1051
01:29:51,820 --> 01:29:54,493
Then what happens
if I get jailed for this?

1052
01:29:54,523 --> 01:29:56,391
What happens to you?

1053
01:29:56,592 --> 01:29:59,231
Livin' beneath the bars?

1054
01:29:59,261 --> 01:30:00,299
But what if you don't?

1055
01:30:00,329 --> 01:30:02,534
Don't get jailed for this?

1056
01:30:02,564 --> 01:30:04,899
Then we just live
with a scandal.

1057
01:30:05,167 --> 01:30:07,702
Small towns don't ever forget.

1058
01:30:25,053 --> 01:30:27,155
Mommy, I'm okay.

1059
01:30:28,423 --> 01:30:31,960
If I don't leave today,
I'll leave soon.

1060
01:30:33,662 --> 01:30:36,735
So don't do this for me.

1061
01:30:36,765 --> 01:30:40,101
Don't hide behind me.

1062
01:30:42,838 --> 01:30:45,073
What do you need to do?

1063
01:30:49,778 --> 01:30:51,980
Dupre.

1064
01:30:55,884 --> 01:30:58,153
He was so kind to me.

1065
01:30:59,821 --> 01:31:04,058
God! I thought for a second
he might be able to save me.

1066
01:31:07,562 --> 01:31:09,364
Maybe he did.

1067
01:31:18,640 --> 01:31:21,643
I should have left
a long time ago.

1068
01:31:28,016 --> 01:31:29,951
Let's get out of here.

1069
01:31:48,203 --> 01:31:50,205
Are you scared?

1070
01:31:53,875 --> 01:31:55,376
No.

1071
01:31:56,511 --> 01:31:59,347
First time in a long time.

1072
01:32:01,583 --> 01:32:03,618
Not scared at all.

1073
01:33:31,273 --> 01:33:33,741
One, two, three...

